==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissonance
<hw>Dis"so*nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dissonantia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>dissonance</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A mingling of discordant sounds; an inharmonious combination of
sounds; discord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Filled the air with barbarous <qex>dissonance</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Want of agreement; incongruity.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissonancy</ent>⟦br⟧
